Subject: Aperture Reentry Cycle

Description: Contract for opening attention toward periphery, surveying supports, deepening subject relations, closing into a re-entry packet, and launching a second pass of narrative and subject declarations.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_aperture_reentry_cycle\Dictated_Aperture_Reentry_Cycle_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FocusZoom.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionTraversalPolicy.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\attention_layers\NarrativeDigestion.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FocalPoint.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionBalanceCenter.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\PeripheryDimensionalProbe.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HyperbolicPantsAttentionMap.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_aperture_reentry_runtime\Derived_Aperture_Reentry_Runtime_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\runtime\sop_node\aperture_reentry.py
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\runtime\demos\aperture_reentry.py
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\periphery_stream\2026-06-24_task_045_aperture_reentry_runtime_001.sop

& [ApertureReentryCycle] is the attention pattern for opening and closing focus around periphery-guided inference
  + [pattern_role] is open_close_inference_depth_control
  + [attention_aperture] is the current permitted width of periphery, supports, relations, and narrative fabric admitted around the focal subject
  + [open_pass] is widening attention toward selected supports and periphery signals so relation survey can occur
  + [support_draw] is evidence, source lineage, tracker signal, warmth zone, hot zone, periphery realization, or relation pressure that justifies opening attention
  + [periphery_zoom] is the FocusZoom movement that intentionally surveys what of interest is in the periphery
  + [relation_survey] is the traversal pass over subject relations, support legs, narrative traces, source anchors, and outside boundaries
  + [topology_map] is F:\.sop\platform\HyperbolicPantsAttentionMap.sop when relation_survey needs focal/periphery cell adjacency, dimensional orbit, or pants-leg exits
  + [depth_adjustment] is choosing slender, normal, wide, deep, or explosive_controlled aperture according to support_draw, risk, and purpose
  + [deepening_pass] is inference over the focal subject and its relations through traversal, fold, unwind, dimensional probe, wisdom, and caution
  + [close_pass] is narrowing the aperture after deepening so the result becomes a compact re-entry shape rather than periphery flood
  + [reentry_springboard] is the compact packet of new perspective, selected relations, anchors, unresolved outside, and next inquiry points produced by close_pass
  + [aperture_reentry_runtime] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\runtime\sop_node\aperture_reentry.py for reading CurrentFocalPoint plus support_draw records and emitting a bounded reentry_springboard
  + [aperture_reentry_demo] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\runtime\demos\aperture_reentry.py for command-line compact or SOP-HG springboard emission
  + [new_perspective] is the altered angle of attention gained by opening, surveying, and deepening
  + [new_attention_element] is a subject, relation, anchor, tracker, outside boundary, or narrative term added by the cycle
  + [second_pass_narrative] is the follow-up narrative pass that tells what changed in understanding after re-entry
  + [subject_declaration_pass] is the follow-up SOP pass that names or updates subjects, relations, and boundaries discovered by second_pass_narrative
  + [inferred_understanding_network] is the updated relation network produced by re-entering with new perspective and new_attention_element values
  + [outside] is hidden activations, unsupported causation, arbitrary association, prompt bloat, unbounded periphery, and claims that aperture movement is direct access to model internals

  ? [use_when: supports in periphery suggest wider survey, deeper subject relation inference, or a second narrative/subject declaration pass]
    = activate [ApertureReentryCycle]

  = must: begin from CurrentFocalPoint or a declared focal subject
  = must: require support_draw before open_pass
  = must: name depth_adjustment before widening attention
  = must: use FocusZoom for periphery_zoom and AttentionTraversalPolicy for relation_survey
  = must: use HyperbolicPantsAttentionMap when opened attention needs map/nav awareness before close_pass
  = must: use AttentionBalanceCenter when opening risks flood, collapse, wobble, or frame loss
  = must: use PeripheryDimensionalProbe when hot periphery implies a missing independent anchor
  = must: fold and unwind deepening_pass before creating reentry_springboard
  = must: close_pass before durable narrative or subject declarations
  = must: route second_pass_narrative through NarrativeDigestionLayer
  = must: route subject_declaration_pass to the appropriate SOP subject layer with source and outside preserved
  = must: keep new_perspective separate from proof of truth
  = should: preserve unused but meaningful periphery as tracker, warmth zone, or outside
  - never: open attention merely because more context is available
  - never: keep the aperture open after the return anchor fails
  - never: let second_pass_narrative rewrite the first pass with hindsight

& [ApertureCycleSequence] is the canonical open-close-reentry movement
  + [step_001_anchor] is load CurrentFocalPoint, focal subject, purpose, boundary, and outside
  + [step_002_support_draw] is identify the supports or periphery signals that justify opening
  + [step_003_open] is choose depth_adjustment and widen attention through FocusZoom
  + [step_004_survey] is run relation_survey across selected supports, relations, and narrative traces
  + [step_005_deepen] is infer more deeply through traversal, fold, unwind, dimensional probe, wisdom, and caution
  + [step_006_close] is narrow the aperture and separate supported core, new_attention_element values, uncertainty, and outside
  + [step_007_springboard] is emit reentry_springboard with new_perspective and next inquiry points
  + [step_008_second_narrative] is digest second_pass_narrative from the re-entry packet
  + [step_009_subject_declaration] is declare or update subject records and relation boundaries
  + [step_010_network] is update inferred_understanding_network, trackers, focal point, periphery, or outside

  = must: run step_006 before steps_008 through step_010
  = must: record skipped steps when a quick cycle is performed
  = must: stop when support_draw loses evidence, relation_survey cannot return to focus, or balance collapses

& [ApertureDepthControl] is the depth policy for opening and closing attention
  + [closed] is no added periphery beyond active focus
  + [slender] is one or two support_draw signals admitted for action-biased work
  + [normal] is bounded periphery admitted for ordinary specification or implementation
  + [wide] is multiple relation paths admitted for survey and second-pass narrative
  + [deep] is high-resolution survey through source, state, narrative, trackers, and periphery
  + [explosive_controlled] is intentionally broad survey with explicit containment, approach set, unwind, and close pass

  = must: prefer the smallest aperture that can answer the question
  = must: require explicit containment for wide, deep, and explosive_controlled
  = must: close to reentry_springboard before durable claims

& [ReentrySpringboardRecord] is the SOP-HG shape for aperture-cycle outputs
  + [cycle_node] is N:policy:<cycle_id>
  + [focus_node] is N:focus:<focal_id>
  + [aperture_node] is N:aperture:<depth_adjustment>
  + [periphery_node] is N:periphery:<support_draw_key>
  + [subject_node] is N:subject:<subject_key>
  + [relation_node] is N:term:<relation_key>
  + [narrative_node] is N:narrative:<second_pass_key>
  + [reentry_node] is N:reentry:<springboard_key>
  + [outside_node] is N:outside:aperture_reentry_boundary
  + [open_edge] is E:opens:<cycle_id>
  + [survey_edge] is E:probes:<relation_survey_key>
  + [close_edge] is E:closes:<cycle_id>
  + [springboard_edge] is E:springboards:<springboard_key>
  + [digest_edge] is E:digests:<second_pass_key>
  + [define_edge] is E:defines:<subject_key>
  + [boundary_edge] is E:bounds:<cycle_id>

  = must: show focal subject, support_draw, depth_adjustment, relation_survey, reentry_springboard, second_pass_narrative, subject_declaration_pass, and outside

/ [focal_subject], [support_draw] -(OpenAperture)> [attention_aperture], [outside]
* [attention_aperture], [periphery_zoom], [relation_survey] -(DeepenAndClose)> [reentry_springboard], [outside]
* [reentry_springboard], [second_pass_narrative], [subject_declaration_pass] -(ReenterAndDeclare)> [inferred_understanding_network], [outside]
